Date Someone Like You Science is challenging the old cliché that opposites attract: Couples and friends tend to share similar personality traits , a study published in the journal Psychological Science finds. Previous decades of research have shown no link between personality similarities for romantic partners or friends, but that may have been because prior studies relied on self-reported questionnaires—now, researchers used actual behavior on social media to discern what people’s personalities are really like. 
Breathe Easy Exposure to dirty air can have serious consequences. People who breathe in air with more fine particulate matter are more likely to die prematurely than those who live with less air pollution, a study from China found. This was due to greater chances of dying from heart disease , high blood pressure , stroke , and chronic obstructive pulmonary disorder (COPD). 
Pop an Aspirin The same drug that can ease your headache might have an even greater benefit: cancer protection. Researchers from the U.S. Department of Veteran Affairs discovered that aspirin can thwart tumor growth . Tumors need new blood vessels to grow, and aspirin may interfere with that process, the scientists say. 
Check Your Cheese Some kinds of Sargento cheese may be contaminated with listeria bacteria , CNN reports. The cheese affected include Sliced Colby-Jack Cheese, Sliced Pepper Jack Cheese, Chef Blends Shredded Taco Cheese, Off The Block Shredded Fine Cut Colby-Jack Cheese and Off The Block Shredded Fine Cut Cheddar Jack Cheese. For more information, and to check specific UPC codes , visit Sargento’s website.
